[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926829&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926829&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

I too have seen this phenomenon.  I have seen records for B.ISI.EDU
showing up as a nameserver for the root in some of my non-root servers
(like VGR).  I would love to know who is sending these bogus records.
I think I can probably teach named to scream when it sees an un-truth
come by.  AOS should then be able to then finger the guilty party!
A quick call to 911 should then solve the problem.

	AOS is safe because it is already a root server and
it doesn't get corrupted.  I am thinking about this very topic right
now as I am busy preparing the next bind.  I hope to have a new version
ready by the middle of next week for Beta testing.  I will try and get
a note out describing what I have done.  I am trying to address most
of the concerns people have raised, though I will not get all of them
in this release.  More work is planned, but an interim release is needed
now.

Suggestions are hereby solicited for types of statistics to gather.

Suggestions are hereby solicited for algorithms of filtering the AR info.

Cheers,
	-Doug-

